[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which is an adapt which is adaptive bitrate streaming. Here\'s how it actually works. So, the source code video gets chopped into two second chunks and it gets chopped at four different quality levels. You can think'

[03:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of it like 1080p quality, 720p, 480p, and 240p. These three different These four quality vid'

[03:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quality levels are for the same video. So, you get four versions. Then a manifest file as well gets sent, which is going to be then a manifest file, a M3U8 file, will also get sent'

[03:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that lists every chunk that lives there. The player is then going to read the manifest file, start at a medium quality, maybe at 720p, and it\'s going to measure your bandwidth'

[03:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in real time. If your signal drops, it\'s going to ask for a 480p file. Signal comes back, it asks for a 1080p. So, this way you never see a spinner and the quality just shifts. That feedback loop right there, that\'s'

[04:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
